    {
      "id": "Q121",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "To ensure equitable comparison across architectures, we implement a standardized training protocol."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q122",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "All SLMs are finetuned using the AdamW optimizer in 20 epochs with a learning rate schedule incorporating 10% linear warmup steps followed by linear decay."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q123",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Early stopping (patience=5) is adopted, and the dev set performance is monitored."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q124",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Learning rates are carefully calibrated for each architecture type as detailed in Table 10."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q125",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Our empirical investigations demonstrate that slot filling tasks consistently require higher learning rates compared to intent detection tasks specifically, encoder-only models utilize 1 × 10−5/3 × 10−5for intent detection/slot filling respectively, while encoder-decoder architectures necessitate elevated rates of 5 × 10−5/1 × 10−4."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q126",
      "page": 13,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Given the computational constraints of finetuning LLMs, Fully Supervised Fine-Tuning (FSFT) is exclusively performed on the Gemma 2 9B model with 5 epochs."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q127",
      "page": 14,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Based on established SFT practices and task-specific requirements, we use learning rates of 2 × 10−5 and 2.5 × 10−5 for intent detection and slot filling respectively."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q128",
      "page": 14,
      "dimension": "input_content",
      "text": "Training data is constructed from the combined train splits of INJONGO dataset across all 17 languages, with prompts randomly sampled from a pool of 5 predefined templates."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q129",
      "page": 14,
      "dimension": "input_form",
      "text": "All experiments are conducted using full precision (FP32) on NVIDIA H100/L40S GPUs with a consistent batch size of 32, achieved through gradient accumulation when necessary."
    },
    {
      "id": "Q130",
      "page": 14,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Before the final model training, we conducted a comprehensive analysis of learning rate variations to understand their effect on model performance across Intent Detection and Slot Filling tasks."
